This paper deals with routing protocols for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses energy efficiency, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The proposed scheme involves clustering, which could also fall under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of existing protocols, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
